sql:
SELECT contact_id, department_id, primary_contact
FROM contact_department
WHERE contact_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "venerable giants" refers to companies with a long-standing presence and a large workforce;
- "more than a decade's worth of team members" means having more than 10 employees;
- "not been touched by the winds of change within the last year" refers to companies that have not been updated in the database for over a year;
- "how many voices do they still carry in their ancient halls" translates to counting the number of contacts associated with each company.

sql:
SELECT c.first_name, c.last_name, c.job_title, com.company_name
FROM contacts c
INNER JOIN companies com ON c.company_id = com.company_id;
